title: Pullback of one-forms

A map $$f\colon M\to N$$ induces $$f_*=\D_p f\colon \T_p M\to \T_{f(p)} N,$$ at each $$p\in M$$ which in turn induces a [[dual map|Duale Abbildung]] $$f^*\coloneqq (\D_p f)^*\colon\T_{f(p)}^* N\to \T_p^* M.$$ For $$\omega\in\Omega^1(N),$$ we define $$f^*\omega\in\Omega^1(M)$$ by

$$
(f^*\omega)_p=f^*\left(\omega_{f(p)}\right)\in\T_p^* M.
$$